="alert"><i class="uil uil-exclamation-circle"></i>Link your domain to Cloudflare Pages with DNS CNAME.&nbsp;</div><div class="card"><div class="card-body"><ol class="mb-0"><li>Register and create an account with Cloudflare. Choose Pages from sidebar and select your project.<br><br><a data-glightbox=""><img src="/images/integration/cloudflare/small/cf-pages-edit-project_small.png" alt="prefs createbucket" width="400" height="191"></a><br><br></li><li>When a project is created Cloudflare creates a subdomain using your project name for example youdocms.pages.dev. To link your domain if it is not hosted on CloudFlare edit the project and choose custom domain.<br><br><img src="/images/integration/cloudflare/small/cf-pages-edit-custom-domain_small.png" width="400" height="262" alt="cf-pages-edit-custom-domain_small.png"><br><br></li><li>In order to redirect requests to your main domain to the CloudFlare sub domain you will need to create a CNAME record in your providers DNS. Enter the domain name you require including the prefix. In our case we are using www5.youdocms.com as we are hosting the same site in multiple clouds for testing.<br><br><img src="/images/integration/cloudflare/small/cf-pages-domain-name_small.png" width="400" height="236" alt="cf-pages-domain-name_small.png"><br><br></li><li>Choose the option to create a CNAME record for your existing DNS provider. Note CloudFlare offers very competitive domain name hosting which is non-profit ie CloudFlare only charges the registrar fees. This is great value for money.<br><br><a data-glightbox=""><img src="/images/integration/cloudflare/small/cf-pages-custom-dns_small.png" alt="prefs listbucket" width="400" height="265"></a><br><br></li><li>&nbsp;Lastly copy the CNAME settings and create a new record with your DNS provider. Wait for the DNS changes to propagate and Use the check DNS button to verify the settings to make sure they are correct.&nbsp;<br><br><img src="/images/integration/cloudflare/small/cf-pages-cname_small.png" width="400" height="337" alt="cf-pages-cname_small.png"><br><br></li><li>You will be notified by email when the DNS is updated and teh cusotm domain is active. To deploy your site see Cloudflare Depoyment.<br><br><img src="/images/integration/cloudflare/small/cf-pages-domain-active_small.png" width="400" height="171" alt="cf-pages-domain-active_small.png"></li></ol></div></div></section></div></div></div></div><footer class="bg-dark text-inverse"><div class="container py-13 py-md-15"><div class="row gy-6 gy-lg-0"><div class="col-md-4 col-lg-3"><div class="widget"><img class="mb-4" src="/images/cms_logo.png" srcset="/images/cms_logo@2x.png 2x" alt=""><p class="mb-4">© 2021 YouDo Ltd.<br class="d-none d-lg-block">All rights reserved.YouDoCMS is not affiliated with or endorsed by Open Source Matters, the Joomla! Project, Wordpress.org or Wordpress.com. Joomla!® is a registered trademark of Open Source Matters, Inc.</p></div></div><div class="col-md-4 col-lg-3"><div class="widget"><h4 class="widget-title text-white mb-3">Get in Touch</h4><address class="pe-xl-15 pe-xxl-17">Made in Upminster, Essex, United Kingdom</address><a href="mailto:info@youdocms.com">info@youdocms.com</a><br>+44 (020) 7148 3322</div></div><div class="col-md-4 col-lg-3"><div class="widget"><h4 class="widget-title text-white mb-3">Learn More</h4><ul class="list-unstyled mb-0"><li><a href="about-us">About Us</a></li><li><a href="privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a></li><li><a href="terms-and-conditions">Terms and Conditions</a></li><li><a href="index.html">Home</a></li></ul></div></div><div class="col-md-12 col-lg-3"><div class="widget"><div class="widget"><h4 class="widget-title text-white mb-3">Our Community</h4><p class="mb-5">Subscribe to our forum for news and support.</p><div class="newsletter-wrapper"><div id="mc_embed_signup2"><a href="https://forum.youdocms.com/login" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank">Community</a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></footer><div class